From: "Darrick J. Wong" <djwong@kernel.org>
Date: Sun, 30 Jan 2022 08:53:17 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] xfs: return errors in xfs_fs_sync_fs
Git-commit: 2d86293c70750e4331e9616aded33ab6b47c299d
Patch-mainline: v5.17-rc3
References: git-fixes

Now that the VFS will do something with the return values from
->sync_fs, make ours pass on error codes.

Signed-off-by: Darrick J. Wong <djwong@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
Reviewed-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Acked-by: Christian Brauner <brauner@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Anthony Iliopoulos <ailiop@suse.com>

---
 fs/xfs/xfs_super.c |    6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/fs/xfs/xfs_super.c
+++ b/fs/xfs/xfs_super.c
@@ -754,6 +754,7 @@ xfs_fs_sync_fs(
 	int			wait)
 {
 	struct xfs_mount	*mp = XFS_M(sb);
+	int			error;
 
 	/*
 	 * Doing anything during the async pass would be counterproductive.
@@ -761,7 +762,10 @@ xfs_fs_sync_fs(
 	if (!wait)
 		return 0;
 
-	xfs_log_force(mp, XFS_LOG_SYNC);
+	error = xfs_log_force(mp, XFS_LOG_SYNC);
+	if (error)
+		return error;
+
 	if (laptop_mode) {
 		/*
 		 * The disk must be active because we're syncing.
